Notification Engine

Running the project.

Change the following attributes in the application.conf file.

The Twilio Account ID for using the Twilio API:

twilio.accountSid


The Twilio authentication token supplied by Twilio for the account being used:

twilio.authToken


A callback address for status updates from the Twilio API:

twilio.callbackAddress="http://42a2173c.ngrok.io"

Note: this will be the base URL for the application.For testing purposes,
ngrok was used to create an address (https://ngrok.com/).


Update the database configurations to the database being used.

db.default.url="jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/notification_engine"
db.default.driver="com.mysql.jdbc.Driver"
db.default.user="[CHANGE_ME]"
db.default.pass="CHANGE_ME"


After updating the application.conf file run the file conf/updated_schema.sql.

Evolutions can also be used to update the schema - a evolution file is provided as conf/evolutions.default/1.sql
